Spiced Lamb Meatballs with Green Raisin Pesto

Pesto:
2 c packed mint leaves
1 c packed flat parsley leaves
1/2 c evoo
3 tbsp golden raisins
1 large garlic clove, roughly chopped
2 tsp fresh lemon juic
1 tsp lemon zest
salt and pepper to taste

In a food processor, combine the mint, parsley, olive oil, raisins, garlic, lemon juice and zest. Season with salt and pepper. Pulse until smooth. Transfer to a bowl (makes ¾ c); set aside. Make ahead: Pesto can be made the day before, then should be covered and chilled. Remove from the fridge and bring to room temperature before serving.

Meatballs:
1 lb ground lamb
1 large egg
2/3 c panko
2 tbsp whole milk
1 1/2 tsp salt
1/2 tsp whole coriander, toasted and ground
1/4 tsp ground tumeric
1/4 tsp crushed red pepper flakes
sumac or aleppo pepper for garnish

Preheat the oven to 400°. In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients until everything is evenly mixed. Using your hands, roll the lamb mixture into thirty ½ oz balls and transfer to a parchment lined sheet tray. Bake the meatballs until golden grown and cooked through, 8-10 min.

Assembly:
warm pitas
thinly sliced yellow onions
pickled jalapeños 
mixed fresh herbs (i.e. mint, cilantro, tarragon, and oregano)

Garnish the meatballs with sumac or aleppo pepper and serve on a platter with the pesto, pita, onions, pickled jalapeños  and herbs.

